%N A051051 Denominators of the probability that the convex hull of n+2 randomly chosen points in the unit ball B^n has n+1 vertices (with factor of Pi^n dropped for n even).
%H A051051 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/SylvestersFour-PointProblem.html">Sylvester's Four-Point Problem</a>.
%F A051051 a(n) = denominator(((n+2) / 2^n) * binomial(n+1, (n+1)/2)^(n+1) / binomial((n+1)^2, (n+1)^2/2)) / Pi^(n*(1-(n mod 2))). - _Amiram Eldar_, Oct 28 2025
